      <mods:abstract>
        On December 10, 1968 in Tokyo, Japan, these 294,307,500 yen (then equivalent to US$817,520) became of particularly significance (the amount often rounded up and referred to as 300 million yen) after they were stolen from the Kokubunji branch of the Nihon Shintaku Ginko (bank) in what was the largest heist in Japanese history at the time. Though no longer under the statute of limitations, the thief has yet to come forward or be revealed, and where the money went remains unknown.
      </mods:abstract>
